  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support a Medium assurance declaration, given the breadth of the validation campaign, the low inter-laboratory variability observed (CV < 4%), and the pre-established acceptance bounds being met for all three QoIs. The model risk level of 3 and Medium decision consequence are consistent with a Medium assurance designation per the ASME V&V 40 credibility framework.",
