    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 V&V 40 factors. Twelve factors achieved the required gradation level. One factor (Test conditions) achieved Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3, reflecting the single-condition ASTM F1717 test protocol. The team judged this shortfall acceptable given the narrow COU scope, the direct regulatory relevance of the single test condition, and the strong quantitative agreement across all three QoIs (E/uval range 1.19–1.54, all percentage differences < 10%). The overall evidence base is consistent with a Medium assurance level for a Model Risk Level 3, Medium decision consequence context. Decision: Accepted.",
